{
  "texts": [
    "Annotation was initially mitigated through the utilization of a CNN trained using weakly supervised multi-instance learning.",
    "Furthermore, a dual-stream network design was implemented to acquire comprehensive information at a scale of 5 and specific details at a scale of 20.",
    "The WDRNet model demonstrated a high level of accuracy in identifying tumour images, achieving an accuracy rate of 0.977 at the slide level and 0.953 at the patch level.",
    "ResNet-18 and ResNet-50 were trained on colon gland images in 41.",
    "The models were trained to classify CRC into two classes which are benign and malignant."
  ]
}